dismissalText.long: c Holder b Gabriel
dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal c Holder b Gabriel 80 (116b 7x4 0x6 158m) SR: 68.96

dismissalComment.html: got him! This was on the pads again and Tamim flicked it well, but Holder at short midwicket plucks it out, holding it low to his right. Moved very quickly and very agilely - had to because the ball was travelling. Smart take by the captain

dismissalText.long: c Bravo b Chase
dismissalText.commentary: Soumya Sarkar c Bravo b Chase 73 (68b 9x4 1x6 116m) SR: 107.35

dismissalComment.html: short, pulled flat and hard but straight to the man at deep midwicket, who takes it, nearly over balances, but awareness of where the rope is helps him as he tosses it up and comes back to take it. Umpires consult the third umpire and the replays confirm that it was a clean catch

commentTextItems.html: full toss, straight drive for four and that's the match

commentPostTextItems.html: Due to a technical problem, we were unable to bring you a more detailed coverage of this match. Thanks for joining. That's all from us for tonight

Three fifties, three fifty run stands, needless to say that was a romp. Set up by the openers, who added 144 without much trouble, before Shakib al Hasan joined in, with a run-a-ball 61 and finished the game off in Mushfiqur Rahim's company

dismissalText.commentary: Roston Chase c Mustafizur Rahman b Mashrafe Mortaza 51 (62b 2x4 1x6 85m) SR: 82.25
